                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 23: India has imposed up to 30 per cent duty on import of key aluminium products from China to protect the domestic industry against cheap shipments. The revenue department has notified 12-14 per cent duty on aluminium flat sheets and 25-30 per cent duty on foils. The government has announced further cuts in customs duty on shipments from Singapore as part of an agreement to phase out duties on imports from the country.                            
	 New Delhi, June 23: India has attracted $2.34 billion of foreign investments in April, a rise of 19.3 per cent over the previous month, signalling confidence of foreign investors in the countrys economy. FDI inflow in April was, however, lower than that in the same period last fiscal. The inflows in April and March last fiscal were $3.74 billion and $1.96 billion, respectively.                             
	 New Delhi, June 23: The shipping ministry today came out with a draft bill for establishment of a Major Ports Regulatory Authority, which will fix tariffs for facilities and services provided by major ports and monitor performance of ports managed by private operators.                                                                                                                           
